owl:Class.rdfs:label: Genre
owl:Class.skos:definition: An expressive style of music.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Album
owl:Class.skos:definition: An album is a collection of audio recordings issued as a collection on compact disc (CD), vinyl, audio tape, or another medium.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Car
owl:Class.skos:definition: a road vehicle.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: City
owl:Class.skos:definition: A relatively large and permanent settlement, particularly a large urban settlement

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: compound according to VADER Sentiment analysis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Compound

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: The country where the thing is located.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Country
Imagery
owl:Class.skos:definition: Imagery is the literary term used for language and description that appeals to our five senses. When a music artist attempts to describe something so that it appeals to our sense of smell, sight, taste, touch, or hearing; he/she has used imagery.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Irony
owl:Class.skos:definition: The use of irony in literature refers to playing around with words such that the meaning implied by a sentence or word is actually different from the literal meaning. Often irony is used to suggest the stark contrast of the literal meaning being put forth. The deeper, real layer of significance is revealed not by the words themselves but the situation and the context in which they are placed.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Literary_Device
owl:Class.skos:definition: literary device is a technique a writer uses to produce a special effect in their writing.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Litote
owl:Class.skos:definition: Litotes are a figure of speech consisting of an understatement in which an affirmative is expressed via the negative of its contrary.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Lyrics
owl:Class.skos:definition: Associates lyrics with a musical work

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: Bayerische Motoren Werke AG, commonly referred to as BMW is a German multinational company which produces automobiles and motorcycles.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Mercedes_Benz
Metonomy
owl:Class.skos:definition: A metonymy is a word or phrase that is substituted for a more formal word or phrase to which it is related.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Music_Artist
owl:Class.skos:definition: A person or a group of people (or a computer :-) ), whose musical creative work shows sensitivity and imagination.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Music_Group
owl:Class.skos:definition: Group of musicians, or musical ensemble, usually popular or folk, playing parts of or improvising off of a musical arrangement.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Musical_Work
owl:Class.skos:definition: Distinct intellectual or artistic musical creation.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: negative according to VADER Sentiment analysis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Negative

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: neutral according to VADER Sentiment analysis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Neutral
Palindrom
owl:Class.skos:definition: A word or phrase spelled the same backwards or forwards.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pangrammatic
owl:Class.skos:definition: A sentence (or verse, or song) that includes all the letters of the alphabet. Like palindromes, they’re hard to find in songs.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Person
owl:Class.skos:definition: A person (alive, dead, undead, or fictional).

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Place
owl:Class.skos:definition: Immobile things or locations.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Pleonasm
owl:Class.skos:definition: Pleonasm is a rhetorical device where one or more redundant words are used consecutively in a phrase to express an idea.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Polysyndeton
owl:Class.skos:definition: Creating a list by adding a conjunction in between all the terms on the list. The opposite of asyndeton.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Portmanteau
owl:Class.skos:definition: Portmanteau is simply a blending of two or more words(including their sounds and meanings) into a singular new word.

owl:Class.rdfs:comment: positive according to VADER Sentiment analysis.
owl:Class.rdfs:label: Positive
Release_Date
owl:Class.skos:definition: Time-Spans are used to define the temporal extent of instances in the ontology and any other phenomena valid for a certain time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Sentiment
owl:Class.skos:definition: The sentiment of a piece of text is its positivity or negativity, and sentiment analysis gives an objective idea of whether the text uses mostly positive, negative, or neutral language.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Similie
owl:Class.skos:definition: A simile is where one thing is compared to another to help with describing something.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Spoonerism
owl:Class.skos:definition: A spoonerism is a play on words in which the sounds of two or more words are transposed.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Synecdoche
owl:Class.skos:definition: When a part of something stands in for the whole thing OR the whole thing stands in for the part.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Synethesia
owl:Class.skos:definition: In literature, synesthesia refers to a technique adopted by writers to present ideas, characters, or places in such a manner that they appeal to more than one sense, like hearing, sight, smell, and touch at a given time.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Tmesis
owl:Class.skos:definition: Tmesis involves the separation of the parts of compound word by intervening words.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Topic
owl:Class.skos:definition: Thing or concept that is being discussed, described, or dealt with.

owl:Class.rdfs:label: Zeugma
owl:Class.skos:definition: Tmesis involves the separation of the parts of compound word by intervening words.
